Aspirants in Kisumu have been warned against hiring youths to cause chaos during nominations and campaigns.County Commissioner Mohammed Maalim yesterday said they will deal firmly with any politician found hiring goons to disrupt peace during the electioneering period.He said the county security team has identified violence hotspots.&ldquo;We are keenly monitoring these areas to enable us to be proactive in containing possible cases of political violence,&rdquo; Maalim said.He was addressing a consultative peace forum, where the aspirants pledged to preach peace. Kisumu Clergy Fellowship chairperson Bishop Winnie Owiti urged the aspirants not to use youths to cause chaos.